       aaddddffttiinnffoo  reads a troff font file and adds some additional font-metric
       information that is used by the groff system.  The font file  with  the
       information  added  is written on the standard output.  The information
       added is guessed using some parametric information about the  font  and
       assumptions about the traditional troff names for characters.  The main
       information added is the heights and depths of characters.  The _r_e_s and
       _u_n_i_t_w_i_d_t_h  arguments should be the same as the corresponding parameters
       in the DESC file; _f_o_n_t is the name of the file describing the font;  if
       _f_o_n_t ends with II the font will be assumed to be italic.

